<subSubSection id="C31D6540FF9ABD16FD49FEC9FCDBFD52" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB836CBFF9ABD16FD49FEC9FCDBFD52" blockId="6.[717,1309,299,722]" lastBlockId="6.[98,1308,727,2377]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">
Classically treated as a member of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D48FF9ABD16FCE0FE22FC45FE14" box="[871,990,413,446]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Rhizomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rhizomys</taxonomicName>
. Wang Yingxiang in 2003 treated ward: as a distinct species and named neowardi as a new subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D48FF9ABD16FD7EFDABFCDAFD9F" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1921" box="[761,833,532,565]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Rhizomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wardi">wardi</taxonomicName>
. Subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D48FF9ABD16FC7AFDABFBC1FD9F" authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1871" box="[1021,1114,532,565]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Rhizomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vestitus">vestitus</taxonomicName>
is also sometimes treated as a distinct species. These approaches were not adopted by A. T. Smith in 2008, but presence of multiple species within what is currently recognized as 
<taxonomicName id="4C074D48FF9ABD16FF0BFD68FE8EFD52" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" box="[140,277,727,760]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Rhizomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sinensis">R. sinensis</taxonomicName>
seemslikely. Six subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
